1) POLICY RULES

- The action cell contains a 'token'. (seen in ~all/5 demos)
- The action cell is the topmost 'token' in a contiguous vertical column of 'token' cells. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- All cells above the action cell in the same column are 'empty'. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is directly above a contiguous cluster of 'token' cells in the same column. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is the highest (smallest row index) 'token' in its column. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is adjacent (up or left) to a region of 'empty' cells. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is the first 'token' encountered when scanning down the column from the top. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is not blocked by any other 'token' above it in the same column. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is part of a vertical cluster of 'token' cells, and removing it will disconnect the cluster above from the rest. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is adjacent (down) to at least one other 'token' cell (except possibly in the last step). (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is never in the leftmost column if that column is empty. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is always in a column where all 'token' cells below it are also 'token' (i.e., no 'empty' gaps below). (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is always the next available 'token' in the rightmost non-empty column. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is never diagonally adjacent to another 'token' unless it is also vertically adjacent. (seen in ~5/5 demos)
- The action cell is always the next in a sequence, proceeding from top to bottom in the rightmost column with 'token's. (seen in ~5/5 demos)

2) COUNTERFACTUAL DISTRACTORS

- 'Token' cells that are not the topmost in their column (i.e., have another 'token' above them) are not chosen.
- 'Token' cells in columns to the left of the rightmost non-empty column are not chosen.
- 'Token' cells that are horizontally adjacent to the action cell but not in the same column are not chosen.
- 'Token' cells that are surrounded by other 'token's on all sides (not at the top of a cluster) are not chosen.
- 'Token' cells that are below other 'token's in the same column are not chosen.

3) GAME DYNAMICS

- When a 'token' cell is removed (clicked), all 'token' cells above it in the same column are also removed in the same step.
- All cells above the action cell in the same column become 'empty' after the action.
- No horizontal or diagonal movement of tokens occurs; only vertical removal.
- Only the column containing the action cell is affected; other columns remain unchanged.
- The size of the contiguous 'token' cluster decreases by the number of tokens removed in the column.
- The process repeats until all 'token's are removed from the grid.
- The action always targets the topmost 'token' in the rightmost non-empty column.
- The environment is deterministic: the same action in the same state always produces the same result.
- No new tokens appear; the grid only transitions from 'token' to 'empty'.
- The game ends when all cells are 'empty'.